<h2 id="using-param-conversion">Using Param Conversion <a class="headerlink" href="param-conversion#using-param-conversion" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>So... doing all of this didn't change <em>anything</em>. So why did I make us do all that?
Let me show you. You might <em>expect</em> me to add a <code>$name</code> argument. But don't! Instead,
type-hint the argument with the <code>Genus</code> class and then add <code>$genus</code>:</p>
