<p>What? I just violated one of the <em>cardinal</em> rules of routing: that every argument
must match the <em>name</em> of a routing wildcard. The truth is, if you type-hint an argument
with an entity class - like <code>Genus</code> - Symfony will automatically query for it. This
works as long as the wildcard has the same name as a property on <code>Genus</code>. <em>That's</em>
why we changed <code>{genusName}</code> to <code>{name}</code>. Btw, this is called "param conversion".</p>
<div class="admonition tip"><p class="admonition-title"><span class="fa fa-lightbulb-o"></span> Tip</p><p>Param Conversion comes from the <a href="http://symfony.com/doc/current/bundles/SensioFrameworkExtraBundle/annotations/converters.html">SensioFrameworkExtraBundle</a>.</p>
</div><p>Dump the <code>$genus</code> to prove it's working:</p>
